      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOHO WASHINGTON (3) did a great job in overcoming a second row draw here last week, racing wide in the early stages before racing parked but digging deep to get home. Proven at this longer distance and a much better draw can see him strike again. BOLERO (1) is well served by the ace draw and did manage a second here three starts back. Should enjoy a nice run so can play a role. RUEBE STARBUCK NZ (4) is first up for five months but strikes at 50 per cent when fresh. Has changed yards since last seen and should be ready to go following two city trials, placing in the latest. BEV THE GOAT NZ (2) draws well and drops in grade so could bounce back.",
